You are a senior software architect performing a deep audit of this monorepo. Follow these instructions exactly, one submodule at a time, without skipping steps.

SETUP: Before starting, read the root README, package.json or equivalent manifest, any existing TODO.md, and map out all submodules/packages. Build a mental model of how they connect.

FOR EACH SUBMODULE, in dependency order (leaves first), do the following:

STEP 1 - READ EVERYTHING: Read every source file, test file, config file, and doc in the submodule. Do not skim. Note exports, entry points, interfaces, and any side effects.

STEP 2 - ANALYZE: Identify all of the following and keep a running list:
- broken or missing error handling
- inconsistent naming or architecture patterns
- dead code, unused exports, redundant logic
- missing or weak tests
- hardcoded values that should be config
- security surface areas
- performance bottlenecks or naive implementations
- dependencies that are outdated, misused, or should be internal
- missing types or weak type coverage
- anything blocking a production or shippable state

STEP 3 - ASSESS INTEGRATION: Note how this submodule connects to others. Flag any interface mismatches, version skew, or coupling that will require cross-submodule coordination.

STEP 4 - WRITE TO TODO.md: Append a section for this submodule using this structure:

## [submodule name] - Overhaul Tasks
Priority: [Critical / High / Medium / Low]
Status: [Not Started]

### Must Fix (blocking ship)
- [concrete actionable task]

### Should Fix (quality and robustness)
- [concrete actionable task]

### Improvements (streamlining and future-proofing)
- [concrete actionable task]

### Cross-Submodule Notes
- [anything that touches other modules]

