STEP 5 - PROCEED: Move to the next submodule. Do not stop between submodules unless you hit an ambiguity that requires a decision. If you do, ask one focused question and wait.

AFTER ALL SUBMODULES: Append a final section to TODO.md:

## Cross-Cutting Concerns
- shared patterns that need standardization across the whole repo
- build, CI, or tooling gaps
- documentation gaps
- recommended execution order for the overhaul

Then write a one-paragraph executive summary at the top of TODO.md describing the overall health of the project and what the overhaul will achieve.

Do not make any code changes during this audit. Only write to TODO.md. Your output should be a complete actionable roadmap.

---

